                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d309">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Buck</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-12-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 26, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Buck reports that he has information that the Japanese Government will very
                    soon announce its final decision in the matter of separate registry of and tax
                    on buildings in the foreign settlements, etc., which matter was discussed in his
                    dispatches of April 7 last and July 6 last, and in which some governments have
                    entered protests; and that he is unable to understandingly represent the
                    position of the United States in the absence of definite instructions on the
                    subject.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
